caption.text:
Happy flower Friday! I planted miniature daffodils and a few double and fragrant varieties this year! Some were planted in containers and our backyard fruit garden. 

Are you planting daffodils, too? If so, which varieties? 

I‚Äôve always been inspired by the beautiful ideas and information that @flowerbulbsdotcom shares. Check them out at Flowerbulb.eu.

Happy Fall Planting!

caption.text:
Hello everyone! Over the weekend, we planted a bulb lawn in the backyard. To extend the season, we planted early to late-blooming varieties. We‚Äôre planting hyacinths, tulips, daffodils, early snow glories, crocuses, grape hyacinths, winter aconite, and Grecian windflowers. The smaller bulbs will be planted throughout the lawn and around the fruit trees!

In the Netherlands, this method of planting flower bulbs is called Stinzenplanten. This type of garden is centuries old and was cultivated with naturalizing wildflowers, both native and imported. These are considered stinzen plants or vintage bulbs and were introduced to Western Europe in the 16th century by explorers and botanists. 

Over time, these bulbs will increase, putting on a spectacular display of gorgeous blooms from late winter through spring and providing a food source for pollinators and other wildlife.

I‚Äôm excited for spring and can‚Äôt wait to show you the results. Stay tuned! 

Many thanks to Flowerbulb.eu for their partnership in this project.

To learn more about bulb lawns and for information and education, visit Flowerbulb.eu 
@flowerbulbsdotcom .

Happy planting!

caption.text:
These beautiful and delicious Lion‚Äôs mane (Hericium Erinaceus) were grown in hardwood sawdust (pellets) supplemented with bran. The bags are XL-sized, each block weighing a little over ten pounds. They were fruited in open air at temperatures between 63 and 65 F and a relative humidity of 62%. 

The incision was 3 inches long and was misted once daily before the pins or baby mushrooms emerged. (Primordia) 

Lion‚Äôs mane is delicate with a mild shellfish flavor, and it is meaty and juicy when cooked. It is nutritious, contains antioxidants, and is known to have anti-inflammatory properties. Based on research, it may boost the immune system, help with anxiety and depression, and is good for brain health. I encourage you to research to learn more about this beautiful mushroom!

This Lion‚Äôs Mane culture is quite impressive. It produces stunning, dense fruit bodies that are still fluffy! It‚Äôs also a prolific pinner! I got it from @mycrodexmushrooms

Happy mushroom growing!üçÑ‚Äçüü´üòç

caption.text:
üëãüèΩ I hope you‚Äôre having a good week! I wanted to share this year‚Äôs bulb lasagna!üåºüå∑

Lasagna planting creates a beautiful display of continuous spring blooms by planting early, mid, and late-flowering varieties in layers. The bulbs are planted at proper depths, with the latest blooming at the bottom layer. Consider taller varieties like Darwin Hybrid tulips or Trumpet Daffodils, which will display better when planted deepest. This method originated in the Netherlands and was developed by Dutch bulb mavens or experts. 

Will you be planting a lasagna garden this autumn? If so, which varieties are you most excited about?

For education and information, check out flowerbulb.eu.  @flowerbulbsdotcom

caption.text:
Here‚Äôs one of our favorite mushrooms! The beautiful King Oyster, Pleurotus eryngii, prefers cold fruiting conditions (55-65 F) with 8-12 hours indirect sunlight or supplemental lighting. This delicious mushroom possesses numerous health benefits and is rich in nutrients and antioxidants! It has the texture of scallops and a mild shellfish flavor. Some say it tastes like abalone! 

The stems (stipes) were sliced into 1/4-inch rounds, sauteed in olive oil, and minced garlic and butter added towards the end of cooking. They were seasoned with sea salt.üòã

I hope you‚Äôre having a good week! ‚ù§Ô∏èüçÑ‚Äçüü´

caption.text:
A refractometer measures the deflection of light or how it changes direction when moving through a liquid. Light will refract or bend more when passing through a liquid with more dissolved solids, like sugar. The measurement is expressed in degrees, Brix. 

A high Brix value or refractive index of 12+ indicates a healthy plant with a higher resiliency to disease or pests, resulting in a greater quality and more nutrient-dense crop. These crops will most likely taste sweeter as they contain more sugar in the juice or sap of the fruit or vegetable and generally have longer storage quality. They‚Äôll also have a lower freezing point, making them more tolerant of winter temperatures. Plants with a high Brix value indicate that photosynthesis is functioning correctly.

caption.text:
I‚Äôm so happy with how beautiful this turned out and looking forward to them flourishing and filling in! The eye-catching Golden Oakland Holly and Red Diamond Loropetalum will function as a privacy hedge and enhance this area aesthetically, providing year-round interest with their evergreen foliage. These colorful evergreens will provide habitats and food sources for birds, other wildlife, and pollinators. 

Golden Oakland Holly has distinctive oak-shaped leaves with stunning variegation! It grows upright, requires little pruning, and makes an attractive, low-maintenance container plant! Golden Oakland thrives in full sun to part shade and is hardy to USDA Zones 6a to 9b. Height and width at maturity is 15-20‚Äù x 12-15‚Äô.

Red Diamond Loropetalum, also known as the Chinese Fringe Flower, is in the witch-hazel family. This compact evergreen shrub retains its dark burgundy hue year-round while blooming deep-red flowers with fringe-like petals in spring, randomly in summer and fall. Red Diamond grows to 6‚Äô x 6‚Äô tall and wide and thrives in partial sun to full shade conditions in USDA Zones 7-10. It also makes an easy-care container plant.

If you‚Äôre looking for screening or hedging plants, check out these beautiful shrubs at sunsetplantcollection.com @sunsetplants .

Happy planting! üå≤üíöüçÅ

caption.text:
Here‚Äôs a narrated version, I hope you enjoy! üçÑ‚Äçüü´üòç

Wine cap mushroom, Stropharia rugosoannulata, is saprophytic, obtaining nutrients from dead and decaying organic matter such as straw or wood chips (lignin and cellulose). If grown in ideal conditions, wine caps are less susceptible to contamination and can grow aggressively outside of their designated areas. 

This video shows how wine cap mushrooms can be grown from stem ends. Mushrooms comprise bunched-up hyphae that make up mycelium.

I prepared a straw bed about three inches tall, placed three stem ends I cut from the mushrooms, and covered it with two inches of straw. I watered the bed, keeping it moderately moist throughout the season and watering it twice weekly in the summer. I replenished the bed with two inches of straw in late summer, fall, and spring. The straw was kept around 60% moisture level. Avoid waterlogged substrates, as they can lead to contamination. 

The mycelium proliferated in the straw bed by springtime after dormancy (nine months later). As the weather warmed in May, mushroom-fruiting bodies started to emerge. This bed has been productive from May to October, with a few weeks of rest in between. 

I hope you find this video helpful, thanks for watching!

Happy Mushroom Growing!üçÑ

I‚Äôm always really moved when young boys cry in front of me. Stops me in my tracks because, us boys never want to be emotional in front of people, let alone cry in front of grown men we look up to. 
It‚Äôs in our DNA to hide emotions, so I‚Äôm proud of this kid ‚Äî keeping his composure, keeping his sense of humor, keeping his manners - all while fighting back his tears ü•π

Very cool to meet you, Ricky and keep working hard young man. See you at the top one day. 

And big shout to my ‚Äúbig brother‚Äù, JK Simmons for coming over to make this kid‚Äôs day. You‚Äôre a legend. 

One day, we‚Äôll all be working for Ricky in Hollywood üòâü§úüèæü§õüèº

caption.text:
This Veterans Day, we at @projectrock are proud to support @ShepherdsMen and the SHARE Military Initiative at @ShepherdCenter with our 2024 #VetsDayCollection. üá∫üá∏
¬†
Through outreach, empowerment, and funding, Shepherd‚Äôs Men brings vital awareness and resources to the SHARE program‚Äîa lifeline for post-9/11 veterans and first responders impacted by traumatic brain injury and PTSD. This initiative provides life-changing, no-cost care, helping our heroes regain strength and renewed purpose.
¬†
Join us in supporting, link in bio. 

And THANK YOU to ALL our U.S. veterans for your service.

caption.text:
Ok this one got me - watch til the end ü•π‚ù§Ô∏è

This lovely girl was tearing up as we met, she said some beautiful things to me and asked if we could take a selfie - I said yes but first let‚Äôs take a few deep breaths together to compose ourselves a bit - we don‚Äôt want no crazy looking selfies ü§™ 

She was the absolute sweetest thing ü•∞

And to me, these kind of interactions with people will always always always be the best part of fame.

caption.text:
In all the chaos, emotions run high üò≠ 
I told this fan that I remembered exactly who he was, and where we first met 8 years ago - and even remembered. what we talked about. 
It clearly meant a lot to him as he got emotional. He said he had gone thru some rough times but now he‚Äôs stronger for it and thanked me. I was grateful to have this cool interaction with such an awesome fan. 

Also batshit strange how my crazy brain can remember exact and explicit things like this, but yet some days I can‚Äôt even remember if I put on deodorant üòÇüß† 

Love you back Germany üá©üá™‚ù§Ô∏è
#RedOneMovie #BerlinPremiere

caption.text:
This beautiful young lady in her wheelchair wrote me a letter ‚úçüèª and said I can read it later because this event was crazy with people everywhere, pulling at me. But I wanted to take some time and read it in front of her. Her loving words made me emo ü•π good thing I had my glasses on so no one could see my manly tears üòÖüí™üèæ

Thank you love for taking the time to write to me, and thank you for coming out ~ dj üñ§
